# North star & architecture decisions (pod-noir)

The **constitution** is **[docs/pod-noir-northstar.md](docs/pod-noir-northstar.md)**. The **decision log** is **[docs/architecture-decisions.md](docs/architecture-decisions.md)**. Update them in the **same task** when behavior or intent changes materially—do not defer to a “docs pass later.”

## Update **northstar** when you change

- **Identity / learning model** — who it’s for, observe→accuse→solve loop, success criteria.
- **World & tone** — Cluster Agency framing, contacts, what carries between cases.
- **REPL contract** — verb set, solve/debrief rules, precinct policy *as product promises*.
- **Cluster contract** — namespace ownership, teardown, what “real cluster” means for players.

Edit the relevant **section**; refresh the **footer** `Last updated` date. If the change contradicts an older **Roadmap** bullet, add a one-line **accuracy note** in the governance block or adjust the roadmap row.

## Append **architecture-decisions.md** when you make *sweeping* changes

Add a **new table row** when the change affects **system-wide behavior** or **contributor contracts**, for example:

- Solve mode / precinct / kubectl guardrails
- Session lifecycle, namespace apply/teardown, victory checks
- CI integration contract (what must pass on main)
- Git hooks strategy (`core.hooksPath`, smoke hooks)
- LLM provider contract (mock vs HTTP, required env)

**Do not** log every bugfix or single-scenario tweak—use **progress** bullets for that.

## If only copy / one scenario / internal refactor

Say briefly that northstar/AD are unchanged (e.g. “Northstar unchanged—single-case copy only”).

